HEADWORD: Weigelia
<hw>Wei*ge"li*a</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So named after C. E.
<etsep>Weigel</etsep>, a German naturalist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A hardy garden shrub (<spn>Diervilla Japonica</spn>) belonging to
the Honeysuckle family, with white or red flowers. It was introduced
from China.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

